fll-live-initscripts (3.10.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * update load balancing for push mirrors.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 26 Dec 2010 14:59:32 +0100

fll-live-initscripts (3.10.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Bump version build-depends on debhelper to >= 8.
  * Enhance note in distro-default's package description about it being
    more than just an empty package.
  * fll_fstab_generator uses UUID=/LABEL= descriptors for non-linuxy
    filesystems, which previously used convenience symlink pathname.
  * Update fll_fstab_generator.8 for new --ignore option.
  * Add fll_blockdev_detect, an experimental utility which could be used
    by fll-live-initramfs to detect block devices and execute aa script
    to probe them for live filesystem.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 23 Nov 2010 00:04:28 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.9.8) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Joaquim Boura ]
  * new option "--ignore" for fll_fstab_generator to ignore the partition
  * with the given UUID.

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * Use column(1) to prettify fstab instead of internally attempting to
    do it. The same probably needs to be done at some stage in fll-
    installer.
  * Add btrfs to linux_filesystem() function of fll_fstab_generator.
  * Extend Joaquim Boura's --ignore feature to allow ignoring by block
    device node or parent block device node by absolute path or basename.
  * Allow the device_wanted() function of fll_fstab_generator to use basename
    like the new device_ignore function.
  * Merge device_wanted and device_ignore functions into device_flagged.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sat, 20 Nov 2010 16:07:51 +1000

