fll-live-initscripts (3.6.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-reboot: simplify a bit by removing pioodl() function for string
    length sorting and instead parsing mounts in reverse order as done in
    sysvinit 2.86.ds1-62. Depend on sysvinit >= 2.86.ds1-64 for fstab-decode.
  * distro-defaults: register interest in /etc/init.d/slim for runlevel
    override handling to be effective. Also add slim to list of overrides
    to be purged in postrm.
  * Fix lintian pedantic errors by calling `set -e' explicitly and not on
    the shebang line.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sat, 18 Jul 2009 16:30:02 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.6.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * X-org 7.4 doesn't evaluate /usr/share/xserver-xorg/pci/ to determine the
    installed graphics cards anymore:
    - drop temporarily shipped PCI IDs in contrib/
    - drop fll_xserver_discover
    - adapt debian/control accordingly.
  * make fll-live-xorgconfig arch=all.

