fll-live-initscripts (3.4.8) unstable; urgency=low

  * parse all files in /etc/modprobe.d/* for potential blacklist entries;
    this does not filter out conffile backups and other cruft.
  * don't append blacklists to udev conffile, but create new
    /etc/modprobe.d/fll-blacklist.conf, if unavoidable. Treat
    fll-blacklist.conf as configuration file under the responsibility of the
    local admin and do not remove it on purge.

