fll-live-initscripts (3.3.35) unstable; urgency=low

  [ Michael Deelwater ]
  * fll-console-setup:
    - new file
  * debian/rules:
    - initscript install rule for fll-console-setup

  [ Kel Modderman ]
  * fll_fstab_generator:
    - handle ps3d* block devices
    - avoid checking if ps3d* are disk devices with udevadm by having the
      is_wanted() function always return 0 for them
    - use vol_id to determine fstype of ps3d* devices
  * fll-live-utils:
    - it is arch: all package
  * fll-console:
    - rename fll-console-setup to fll-console. It is a script to preseed
      console-setup
    - adjust LSB dependencies of fll-locales and fll-console to ensure start
      before scripts which load keymaps early in runelvel S
    - remove hardcoded md5sum from console-setup
    - only save setupcon configuration, let the initscript do the loading of it
      later
  * Merge fll-console into fll-locales. Remove console-data preseeding, just
    preseed console-setup, i only requires XKBLAYOUT.
  * fll-locales:
    - rename SIDUX_MIRROR to FLL_MIRROR, to remain in a neutral namespace
    - try using VGA as default console font
  * Rename fll-hwsetup to fll-bluez, remove the need for hwinfo and simply
    check if a bluetooth class driver has loaded yet. Start later in runlevel
    S.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 19 Oct 2008 07:21:08 +1000

