fll-live-initscripts (3.2.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - reinvent nv override logic, emulating the NVIsSupported() function of
      xf86-video-nv, which is basically a list of device id's that the driver
      _should_ support, but god knows why they are not listed in
      NVKnownChipsets...
    - xserver-xorg-video-geode ships a pci board id list, no need to override
      it either
    - xserver-xorg-video-vmware ships a pci board id list, we only need to
      provide a input device override
    - simplify blocks of code handling virtulbox and vmware
    - cleanup code flow that detects of virtualbox guest support is wanted or
      not

