fll-live-initscripts (3.1.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_fstab_generator:
    - use error=remount-ro mount option for ext2 and ext3 / filesystem
    - use ID_FS_LABEL_SAFE returned by udev_info() as third argument to
      print_fsentry()
    - use a temporary directory to maintain uniquity and sanity of any string
      to be used in fs_spec and fs_file
    - check value returned by sed call in is_mounted() is actually a directory
      before returning it
    - if labels are wanted, use the "safe" label in fs_file
    - major overhaul of print_fsentry()
    - drop scan_partitions() function

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sat, 24 May 2008 22:29:43 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.1.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - revert change in version 3.0.36 introducing device id's of unknown but
      possibly supported boards to contrib/xrandr/nv list, it produced poor
      results on propoerly supported chips.
  * fll_fstab_generator:
    - tweak default mount options so that users may mount/unmount filesystems
      by default.
    - add explicit 'rw' mount option for filesystems which support that
    - reorder mount options of cdrom and floppy devices for consistency

