fll-live-initscripts (3.0.26) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fix typo in previous changelog entry.
  * fll_fshelper:
    - ensure duplicate mount point names are never used, warn and skip any
      device who has been given a mount point name the same as a device before
      it
    - special case device mapper virtual block device mount point names, use
      dm-X as is used in /proc/partitions (we should switch to /sys/block)
    - count disks by comparing the "basename" of each block device sans and
      partition or minor number. Each time in changes, incriment the disk
      number count
    - no longer add commented out tmpfs example

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 15 Apr 2008 22:12:30 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.25) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - add missing vmmouse input device template
    - disable xresprobe and modelines for vmware xorg.conf
  * fll-shell:
    - preseeding of vimrc.local and pager alternative now done at build time
      so removed from the initscript

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Mon, 14 Apr 2008 19:25:44 +1000

