 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Fri, 21 Mar 2008 22:37:54 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.11) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xserver_discover:
    - add driver_prio() as compar() function for scanning of pci.ids dir, give
      radeonhd last preference, otherwise returning versionsort()
    - give ati driver/wrapper last priority when searching pciids for device
      string, this kills 2 birds in one stone. Firstly it allows radeonhd to
      take preference for R500+ drivers, and ensures r128 and mach64 claim
      devices that they support
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - add AMD Geode GX/LX display driver fallback detection, this driver
      doesn't install a pciids list, and probably will not do so in future
    - when removing virtualbox-ose-guest-utils service, look up initscript
      removal command with fll_analyze_initscripts
    - default to vesa, remove this default in near future
  * fll-xdm:
    - tiny cleanup of bits using eval on a subshell output
    - add insert_initscript() as fallback function for when start and stop
      sequence numbers are not returned by fll_analyze_initscripts

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Thu, 20 Mar 2008 23:57:31 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.10) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - write a Device section to xorg.conf containing driver, busid, boardname
      again. Omitting it seems to work fine, but for an upcoming release we
      should try to avoid collateral userspace damage
  * fll_xserver_discover:
    - tiny debug usage cleanup

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Wed, 19 Mar 2008 13:53:22 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.9) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xserver_discover:
    - return an empty XMODULE string when no driver was detected in ids lists
    - use the GNU extension, scandir(3), when searching
      /usr/share/xserver-xorg/pci/ ids lists, it provides convenience
      functions that are very useful
  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - no longer default to 'vesa' driver, if no driver is given, simply do not
      include the device section in xorg.conf, let the server do the work. In
      this case, also do not include Modelines, Modes or frequencies (randr1.2
      like)
    - do not write the driver, busid or boardname to the default device
      section (except for vboxvideo, cheatcode or nv override). Allow the
      xserver to use the same data we hijacked for early detection, to do
      dynamic detection at X startup
    - no longer create a default 'Device' section if no driver, busid or
      boardname were specified as program arguments
    - overhaul nv override logic, add nv_overridable() function to determine
      if we should force nv based on board description + regular expression
    - update contrib/src/nv_driver.c for new G80 pci ids
    - cleanup output when detection monitor settings via probe

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Wed, 19 Mar 2008 03:18:10 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.8) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xserver_discover:
    - put the printing of device variables into the xdisplay() function
    - allow debugging id list contents with -dd
    - do not break on first encounter of VGA class device, instead process all
      devices. As consequence, devices with lowest busid will be preferred
    - break when driver string has been found in ids list

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 18 Mar 2008 12:57:37 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.7) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-adduser:
    - redirect stdout when using fallback method of adding live user to
      various groups
  * distro-defaults:
    - add chrooted() function to postinst maintainer script
    - only attempt to create /etc/default/distro if in a chroot
    - if in a chroot, and insserv is in path, set desktop manager initscript
      to default runlevel configuration after creating overrides
    - create a default /etc/apt/sources.list template it in a chroot, and the
      file doesn't exist yet

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 11 Mar 2008 20:30:28 +1000

