 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 02 Mar 2008 23:28:35 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (3.0.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Bump major release version number.
  * Assimilate the distro-defaults package. Handle the /etc/defaults/distro
    conffile manually (with ucf) in the postinst and postrm scripts.
  * Do the same conffile handling for fll-live-initscripts as for
    distro-defaults, the files are dynamically generated, so just use ucf to
    relate the package to the file, and manage its addition and removal in the
    postinst and postrm scripts.
  * fll-locales:
    - simplify the addition of dynamic variables to /etc/default/fll-locales
    - LANG is more interesting that LANGUAGE when dumping contents to
      /etc/default/fll-locales

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 02 Mar 2008 22:19:57 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.98) unstable; urgency=low

  * Adjust all LSB headers for initial insserv support. Cheat with fll-reboot,
    and use the special keyworkd $all in the Required-Stop declaration.
  * fll-init:
    - fix blacklisting of modules with blacklist= boot param, there was a
      typo.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 02 Mar 2008 01:25:59 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.97) unstable; urgency=low

  * Trim trailing whitespace from ./debian/* on lines containing content.
  * fll-adduser:
    - remove pam_lastlog hack, this will be done in the builder postinst
    - general cleanup, fix some typos
  * fll-init:
    - fix typo in /etc/default/fll-init
    - ensure LSB header declares x-start-before hostname.sh
  * fll-network:
    - remove kppp-noauth hack, do it in the builder
    - declare in LSB header x-start-before networking
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - don't declare stop runlevels in LSB header.
    - make sure we depend on the fll-locales service
  * fll-xdm:
    - if insserv is installed, adjust the LSB headers so ?dm is started in
      runlevel 5 only

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sat, 01 Mar 2008 20:44:48 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.96) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-init:
    - honour nocpufreq cheatcode now that fll-cpufreq is redundant.
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - no need to check package versions for various xserver-video drivers
      anymore.
  * fll_fshelper:
    - rename $disk and $part to $d and $p to avoid variable scope problems
    - add --simulate-live cli option for testing on an installed system, it
      disables local mount detection

