 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 02 Oct 2007 20:39:37 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.6) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xserver_discover:
    - deprecate method of VGA device detection via discover1-data, drop
      dependency on discover1-data
    - use /usr/share/xserver-xorg/pci/*.ids to identify xserver module that
      supports VGA device
    - depend on File::Slurp, read_dir is used now, remove locsmif's emulator
    - add basic cli options for debug and force use of discover1-data
    - use PCI bus address from sysfs string, rather than another lspci lookup
    - do not print vendor name, no point, it is the first part of the board
      name
    - activate warnings against locsmif's advice, forcing some coding style
      choices
  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - merge ps2 and usb templates into imps2 template
    - remove @@VENDORNAME@@ token, not required/handled anymore
  * fll_xinput_discover:
    - adjust to merged ps2/usb template
    - don't output more than one device of type imps2 to fll_xorgconfig, that
      would cause a pointer device conflict
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - remove ref to XVENDORNAME, print XBOARDNAME on own line

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 02 Oct 2007 10:53:45 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll_xinput_discover:
    - really enable usb workaround, forgot to prepend --input to Generic USB
      mouse workaround
    - add input_priority function -> input device priority sorting algorithm
      that ensures CorePointer is elected to a device type that is most likely
      to not be removed.
  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - reinstate support for Virtual, even if only for my own good
    - enhance debug output
    - simplify handling of $protocol for usb/ps2 and synaptics/alps, both
      pairs are handled identically
    - sort $x{mouse} keys numerically
    - remove need for --composite option to require boolean as argument
    - reinstate display subsections for depths 1, 4 and 15
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - source /lib/init/vars.sh for VERBOSE variable
    - use VERBOSE to enable program output, fix use of VERBOSE
  * fll_fshelper:
    - fix help output for -d|--debug option
    - don't bother making backup for once only write
    - no need to explicitly truncate file

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Mon, 01 Oct 2007 20:45:11 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.4) unstable; urgency=low

  * make workaround more clear.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 30 Sep 2007 11:00:00 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - prune some unused cheatcodes
    - enhance output when probing with xresprobe
  * fll_xinput_discover:
    - simplify CorePointer election
    - add a usb mouse "bogus" detection when no usb device is detected, by
    electing a CorePointer, we somehow lose the ability for a usb input device
    to be hotplugged later

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sun, 30 Sep 2007 10:57:05 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.2) unstable; urgency=low

  * remove hardcoded CorePointer/ SendCoreEvents references for pointing devices.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sat, 29 Sep 2007 12:31:18 +0200

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig: fix typo when announcing detected resolution.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sat, 29 Sep 2007 19:04:28 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (2.0.0) unstable; urgency=low

  * Bump major version number.
  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - fix ansi output when announcing XrandR mode
    - just announce the highest res detected by xresprobe
    - fix mga xrandr1.2 support package version
    - turn composite on for ati and intel drivers
  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - elect serial mouse as "CorePointer" in ServerLayout section
    - don't elect CorePointer or SendCoreEvents in ServerLayout section at
    all, just elect the device
    - change --input API, mandatory 4 arguments,
    corepointer={CorePointer,SendCoreEvents} must be given.
    - remove duplicate "CoreKeyboard" from ServerLayout section, it is defined
    in the "Keyboard0" section too
    - append mouse number to name, not prepend (looks a bit better)
    - remove support for --nowheel, we don't use it
    - add a bunch of code comments
    - cleanup the screen template, removing rarely used Display sections of
    depth 1 and 4
    - fix name of tool in heading template
    - add --composite option
  * fll_xinput_discover:
    - readjust logic, detect and put all input devices into XINPUT
    - always attempt to probe proc
    - count %input keys before probing with hwinfo
    - assign a corepointer, logic is very basic, it will select first
    non-removable input device detected to be corepointer
    - if only one input device is detected, make it the CorePointer no matter
    what type it may be
    - hwinfo method now only detects serial input device
    - add a bunch of code comments

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Sat, 29 Sep 2007 17:48:58 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (1.99.08) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-xorgconfig:
    - typo in XNEWMODULE cheatcode verbosity
    - move hwinfo serial mouse detection layer to fll_xinput_discover
    - honor xmouse=serial|smouse cheatcode by passing --serial to
    fll_xinput_discover
    - reenable extensions section, it is required to turn composite on/off
  * fll_xinput_discover:
    - provide fallback detection method via hwinfo when no input devices
    present in /proc/bus/input/devices
    - filter ps2 and usb mice from XINPUT output, the Xserver will
    autoconfigure them.
    - add handling for 'debug' as first argument
    - allow forced probe of serial devices via --serial cli option
    - add getopt handling for debug and serial cli options
  * fll_xorgconfig:
    - do not push coretype to ServerLayout section for all types but
    alps/synaptics touchpads and serial

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Fri, 28 Sep 2007 13:42:51 +1000

