fll-live-initscripts (1.1.9) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-network: remove executable bit from /etc/network/if-up.d/ntpdate to
    avoid funky problems associated with touching the clock. X often blanks
    itself just after logging into KDE, for example.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Wed, 27 Jun 2007 08:16:00 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (1.1.8) unstable; urgency=low

  * fll-cpufreq: no longer tamper with /etc/powersave/*, add cpufreq module to
    /etc/modules instead.
  * fll-locales: add kb field to locale headers that are parsed by sed for
    list argument. Output is install-gui friendly, and we only used sed once!
  * fll-network: try settling for one second rather than two when detecting
    link beat.

 -- Kel Modderman <kel@otaku42.de>  Tue, 26 Jun 2007 17:34:32 +1000

fll-live-initscripts (1.1.7) unstable; urgency=low

  * Allow flldebug= debug aid to be fll-'less. For example, to debug
    fll-cpufreq use flldebug=cpufreq.
  * fll-network: fork child processes to do link beat detection on all
    detected ethernet devices in parallel. Wait for them to return before
    continuing.

